<exercise>
  <statement>
    <p>
      A basket contains 4 red, 5 blue, and 3 green marbles. If 3 marbles are picked up at random, 
      what is the probability that at least one is blue?  
    </p>
  </statement>
 <hint>
  <p>
    Find probability of being no blue marbles, then probability of at least one blue.
  </p>
  <p>
    <me>
      P(No Blue) = \frac{^7C_3}{^{12}C_3}
    </me>
    <me>
      P(B) = 1-P(No Blue).
    </me>  
  </p>
 </hint>
</exercise>



